title: generic_const_exprs: ICE when converting into type related to trait's internal generic const

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(generic_const_exprs)] use std::marker::PhantomData; trait Trait { const CONST: usize; } struct A { _marker: PhantomData, } impl Trait for [i8; N] { const CONST: usize = N; } impl From for A<[i8; N]> { fn from(_: usize) -> Self { todo!() } } impl From> for A { fn from(_: A<[i8; T::CONST]>) -> Self { todo!() } } fn f() -> A where [(); T::CONST]:, { // Usage of `0` is arbitrary let a = A::<[i8; T::CONST]>::from(0); A::::from(a) } fn main() { // Usage of `1` is arbitrary f::<[i8; 1]>(); } ``` Note: ICE does not occur if either of the two lines in `f()` is replaced with `todo!()`; i.e. ```Rust fn f() -> A where [(); T::CONST]:, { let a: A::<[i8; T::CONST]> = todo!(); A::::from(a) } ``` or ```Rust fn f() -> A where [(); T::CONST]:, { let a = A::<[i8; T::CONST]>::from(0); todo!() } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.65.0-nightly (78a891d36 2022-09-06) binary: rustc commit-hash: 78a891d364a7358ed9eb9c93099ba2f3e6817ca6
